This paper deals with the optimization of network performance in multihop MIMO cognitive radio networks, which involves physical-layer characteristics, link-layer mechanisms, network-layer protocols, and transport-layer strategies. Therefore, it could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia). However, since the paper focuses on the energy-efficient cross-layer optimization problem, cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
